      <!--
        Selective self-collision masks. Bit 0 is reserved for the ball/floor.
        Each finger owns one additional bit and accepts every other finger bit,
        but not its own. This enables cross-finger contact while keeping links
        within the same kinematic finger chain from colliding with each other.
        The palm retains the generic collision class so finger mounts do not
        fight the palm at their nominal joint configuration.
      -->
